race.comment: TERRITORY MAN (1) was a good winner two back over 1400m and then was left with too much to do over the mile last start when he didn't get going until late. He steps out in trip again today which doesn't look an issue off what he did last start. Pike sticks and with some more intent this time, he can return to winning ways. SWEET SURRENDER (8) just missed two back before a strong win at Geraldton last time out when the race favourite. She looks a nice mare on the rise and CJP remaining in the saddle is a good push for her chances. Can raise the bar without surprising. FOREVER DREAMING (3) won two back before missing in a photo finish on the quick turnaround most recently. Again on back up today but steps out in trip and creates plenty of interest. GLANCED (10) is building nicely this time in work and has winning claims out in trip. INVINCIBLE THIEF (6) should appreciate coming out in trip once again and has to be included.
